{"scriptures":{"scriptures":[{"chapter":50,"paragraph":324,"verse":1,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050001,"content":"Then Joseph <crossref let=\"v\" cid=\"c01050001.1\"/>fell on his father's face and wept over him and kissed him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":324,"verse":2,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050002,"content":"And Joseph commanded his servants the physicians to <crossref let=\"w\" cid=\"c01050002.1\"/>embalm his father. So the physicians embalmed Israel.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":324,"verse":3,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050003,"content":"Forty days were required for it, for that is how many are required for embalming. And the Egyptians <crossref let=\"x\" cid=\"c01050003.1\"/>wept for him seventy days.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":4,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050004,"content":"And when the days of weeping for him were past, Joseph spoke to the household of Pharaoh, saying, <crossref let=\"y\" cid=\"c01050004.1\"/>\"If now I have found favor in your eyes, please speak in the ears of Pharaoh, saying,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":5,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050005,"content":"My father made me swear, saying, 'I am about to die: in my tomb <crossref let=\"z\" cid=\"c01050005.1\"/>that I hewed out for myself in the land of Canaan, there shall you bury me. ' Now therefore, let me please go up and bury my father. Then I will return. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":6,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050006,"content":"And Pharaoh answered, \"Go up, and bury your father, as he made you swear. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":7,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050007,"content":"So Joseph went up to bury his father. With him went up all the servants of Pharaoh, the elders of his household, and all the elders of the land of Egypt,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":8,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050008,"content":"as well as all the household of Joseph, his brothers, and his father's household. Only their children, their flocks, and their herds were left <crossref let=\"a\" cid=\"c01050008.1\"/>in the land of Goshen.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":9,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050009,"content":"And there went up with him both chariots and horsemen. It was a very great company.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":10,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050010,"content":"When they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond the Jordan, <crossref let=\"b\" cid=\"c01050010.1\"/>they lamented there with a very great and grievous lamentation, and he <crossref let=\"c\" cid=\"c01050010.2\"/>made a mourning for his father seven days.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":11,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050011,"content":"When the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning on the threshing floor of Atad, they said, \"This is a grievous mourning by the Egyptians. \" Therefore the place was named Abel-mizraim;<footnote><i class=\"catch-word\">Abel-mizraim</i> means <i>mourning</i> (or <i>meadow</i>) <i>of Egypt</i></footnote> it is beyond the Jordan.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":12,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050012,"content":"Thus his sons did for him as he had commanded them,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":13,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050013,"content":"for <crossref let=\"d\" cid=\"c01050013.1\"/>his sons carried him to the land of Canaan and buried him in the cave of the field at Machpelah, to the east of Mamre, which Abraham <crossref let=\"e\" cid=\"c01050013.2\"/>bought with the field from Ephron the Hittite to possess as a burying place.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":325,"verse":14,"section_id":73,"block":null,"verse_id":1050014,"content":"After he had buried his father, Joseph returned to Egypt with his brothers and all who had gone up with him to bury his father.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"Jacob's Death and Burial"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":326,"verse":15,"section_id":74,"block":null,"verse_id":1050015,"content":"When Joseph's brothers saw that their father was dead, they said, \"It may be that Joseph will hate us and pay us back for all the evil that we did to him. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God's Good Purposes"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":326,"verse":16,"section_id":74,"block":null,"verse_id":1050016,"content":"So they sent a message to Joseph, saying, \"Your father gave this command before he died,","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God's Good Purposes"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":326,"verse":17,"section_id":74,"block":null,"verse_id":1050017,"content":"'Say to Joseph, Please forgive the transgression of your brothers and their sin, because they did evil to you. ' And now, please forgive the transgression of the servants of <crossref let=\"f\" cid=\"c01050017.1\"/>the God of your father. \" Joseph wept when they spoke to him.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God's Good Purposes"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":326,"verse":18,"section_id":74,"block":null,"verse_id":1050018,"content":"His brothers also came and <crossref let=\"g\" cid=\"c01050018.1\"/>fell down before him and said, \"Behold, we are your servants. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God's Good Purposes"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":326,"verse":19,"section_id":74,"block":null,"verse_id":1050019,"content":"But Joseph said to them, \"Do not fear, for <crossref let=\"h\" cid=\"c01050019.1\"/>am I in the place of God?","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God's Good Purposes"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":326,"verse":20,"section_id":74,"block":null,"verse_id":1050020,"content":"As for you, you meant evil against me, but <crossref let=\"i\" cid=\"c01050020.1\"/>God meant it for good, to bring it about that many people<footnote>Or <i>a numerous people</i></footnote> should be kept alive, as they are today.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God's Good Purposes"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":326,"verse":21,"section_id":74,"block":null,"verse_id":1050021,"content":"So do not fear; <crossref let=\"j\" cid=\"c01050021.1\"/>I will provide for you and your little ones. \" Thus he comforted them and spoke kindly to them.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"God's Good Purposes"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":327,"verse":22,"section_id":75,"block":null,"verse_id":1050022,"content":"So Joseph remained in Egypt, he and his father's house. Joseph lived 110 years.","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Death of Joseph"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":327,"verse":23,"section_id":75,"block":null,"verse_id":1050023,"content":"And Joseph saw Ephraim's children <crossref let=\"k\" cid=\"c01050023.1\"/>of the third generation. The <crossref let=\"l\" cid=\"c01050023.2\"/>children also of Machir the son of Manasseh were <crossref let=\"m\" cid=\"c01050023.3\"/>counted as Joseph's own. <footnote>Hebrew <i>were born on Joseph's knees</i></footnote>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Death of Joseph"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":327,"verse":24,"section_id":75,"block":null,"verse_id":1050024,"content":"And Joseph said to his brothers, \"I am about to die, but <crossref let=\"n\" cid=\"c01050024.1\"/>God will visit you and bring you up out of this land to the land <crossref let=\"o\" cid=\"c01050024.2\"/>that he swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Death of Joseph"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":327,"verse":25,"section_id":75,"block":null,"verse_id":1050025,"content":"Then <crossref let=\"p\" cid=\"c01050025.1\"/>Joseph made the sons of Israel swear, saying, \"God will surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones from here. \"","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Death of Joseph"},{"chapter":50,"paragraph":327,"verse":26,"section_id":75,"block":null,"verse_id":1050026,"content":"So Joseph died, being 110 years old. They <crossref let=\"q\" cid=\"c01050026.1\"/>embalmed him, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt. <end-chapter/>","book":"Genesis","section_title":"The Death of Joseph"}],"x_refs":{"c01050010.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"2 Sam. 1:17","start_ref_id":10001017,"verse_id":1050010,"letter_id":"b"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Acts 8:2","start_ref_id":44008002,"verse_id":1050010,"letter_id":"b"}],"c01050010.2":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"3","start_ref_id":1050003,"verse_id":1050010,"letter_id":"c"}],"c01050020.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"45:5","start_ref_id":1045005,"verse_id":1050020,"letter_id":"i"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"7","start_ref_id":1045007,"verse_id":1050020,"letter_id":"i"}],"c01050008.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"45:10","start_ref_id":1045010,"verse_id":1050008,"letter_id":"a"}],"c01050021.1":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"45:11","start_ref_id":1045011,"verse_id":1050021,"letter_id":"j"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"47:12","start_ref_id":1047012,"verse_id":1050021,"letter_id":"j"}],"c01050013.1":[{"end_ref_id":1049030,"ref_title":"49:29-30","start_ref_id":1049029,"verse_id":1050013,"letter_id":"d"},{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"Acts 7:16","start_ref_id":44007016,"verse_id":1050013,"letter_id":"d"}],"c01050013.2":[{"end_ref_id":null,"ref_title":"23:16","start_